Gasification is a complex process that depends on the number of parameters such as characteristic of waste provided, type of reactor and operating temperature (Arena and Mastellone 2009). On the basis of oxidation medium used, the process can either be carried out in partial oxidation with limited amount of oxygen or in pure oxygen (air rich in oxygen). The syngas produced after the partial oxidation with air has calorific value ranging between 4 and 7 MJ/mN3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
